      • unify

        boolean unify(Object x,
              Object y)
        Check that two object (x and y) unify. This operation convert x and y object to prolog terms and call terms unification. This operation is defined like object unification.
        Parameters:
        x - the term to unify.
        y - the term to unify.
        Returns:
        true if the specified term unify whit the current term, false otherwise.
        Since:
        1.0
